);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,4,1);
$b = random(3,6,1);
$c = random(10,20,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Suppose that \(x = x(t)\) and \(y=y(t)\) are both functions of
\(t\).  If
\[
    y = $a x^2 - 1,
\]
and \(dx/dt = $b\) when \(x = $c\), what is \(dy/dt\)?
$BR
$BR
\(dy/dt\) = \{ans_rule(20) \}
$BR

EOT

$ans = 2*$a*$c*$b;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

ENDDOCUMENT();
